<br>
But, you have definitely made it to the right place.<br>
<br>
The best advice I can give to you is to dive in here with a vengeance. When reading things here, keep in mind that sooo much of what is said is opinions. We all know how varied opinions can be. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Right off the get go I would suggest mana and hp items (such as Jade or Black saphire Jewelry) where possible as they will help more than raw intelligence. Around 30 look to trade those items out for maxed out Int as the higher mana per point of Int (the amount of mana you get from each point of intelligence goes up as your level does) will make it pay off more then. As magicians we're really no where near as gear intensive as other classes.<br>
<br>
You focus items are VERY important. As you get close to each new spell level (IE 3rd lvl, 7th, 11th, 15th, etc...) your pets begin to be very weak in comparison to the mobs you need to fight for exp. Focus items can offset this quite a bit. The visual difference at 34  is also very cool. I love seeing a gnome running around with a pet that is twice his size <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Look for info on them on The Mage Compendium (there is a link to it on the bottom of this page). If your friends and you are all around 16th you can probably take out all the mobs you would need to and still get experience while doing it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
As far as actual playing skills... That's an art you really have to learn as opposed to having someone explain to you <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Here are a few pointers though:<br>
<br>
1. Make an assist key. USE IT ALL THE TIME <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  It will become your next best friend (after your pet of course). I prefer a blank /assist key (without anyones name in the hotkey) for most situations since I can always target the tank with F2-F6. Sometimes if it is a really fast group or we're in hurry I will put a player's name in it. For example, if your groups tank is named &quot;masterkiller&quot; your assist hotkey would read: /assist masterkiller.<br>
<br>
2. Re-map the autoattack key off of the letter &quot;a&quot; to something less often used (I use the &quot;~&quot; symbol) because you will accidentally type an &quot;a&quot; with a NPC targeted and get yourself killed.<br>
<br>
3. Get used to educating your groups on how they can best utilize your abilities because we're one of the least understood classes in the game.<br>
 &quot;No, Masterkiller, I wasn't trying to say you are a bad tank, just that Jibober here can regen his hits 3x as fast as you and we could save the cleric some mana...&quot;<br>
<br>
 &quot;Hey you melee types, here's some band aids. How about you guys bind wounds while waiting on pulls? While you're at it, here are some arrows mister puller&quot;<br>
<br>
etc...<br>
<br>
A good mage is a HUGE asset to a group.<br>
<br>
I think that's probably enough information for you to absorb from me right now (read that as you've read enough of my rambling for now) so I'll go <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Good luck and welcome to Magedom <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
